                    </h3>
                    <p>When using an elastic database pool, you can manage the overall properties of the pool (instead of a single database). The databases in the pool are called elastic databases, which can automatically increase or decrease to meet demands. Databases can be easily added to or deleted from the pool, scaling the databases of an application from a small number to thousands with all costs not exceeding the budget that you control.</p>
                    <p>Elastic database pool is available at “Basic”, “Standard” and “Advanced” service layers. The three layers are distinguished mainly by their general performance measured in <a id="documentation_articles_sql-database-service-tiers_understanding-dtus" href="/documentation/articles/sql-database-service-tiers/#understanding-dtus" style="color:#00a8d9;" target="_blank">eDTU</a>. Please refer to <a id="documentation_articles_sql-database-service-tiers_understanding-dtus" href="/documentation/articles/sql-database-service-tiers/#understanding-dtus" style="color:#00a8d9;" target="_blank">Service Layers of Elastic Database Pool</a> for further information. Elastic Database Model has been officially released online. Customers will continue to enjoy a discount price of 50% for preview versions.</p>
