            <div class="pricing-page-section">
                <div class="more-detail">
                    <h2>FAQs</h2>
                    <em>Expand all</em>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <i class="icon icon-plus"></i>
                            <div>
                                <a id="home_sql_database_question1">What’s the pricing for Azure SQL database?</a>
                                <section>
                                     <p>The total price of a single database (or elastic databases) is equal to the price of DTU (or eDTU) plus the price of any pre-set extra storage. The price of DTU (or eDTU) covers storage with a certain capacity without additional costs. Once the included storage capacity is exceeded, an extra cost can be paid for additional storage capacity under the storage cap. When the needed storage capacity is less than 1 TB, it can be increased by 250 GB; when it is over 1 TB, it can be increased by 256 GB. The price of the extra storage equals the extra storage capacity multiplied by the unit price of the corresponding service layer. DTU or eDTU and any extra storage are charged by the hour.</p>
                                </section>
                            </div>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <i class="icon icon-plus"></i>
                            <div>
                                <a id="SQL_Database_question2">Example of the pricing of a single database pre-set with extra storage</a>
                                <section>
                                    <p>Suppose an S3 database is pre-set with a 1TB storage capacity. Since it has 250GB of fixed storage capacity, its extra storage capacity is: 1TB - 250GB = 774GB. During the preview, the unit price of standard versions is about RMB 0.5406/GB/month, so the price of extra storage is 774GB * RMB 0.5406/GB/month = RMB 418.42/month. Therefore, the total price of the S3 Database is RMB 969.37/month (eDTU) + RMB 418.42/month of extra storage = RMB 1387.79/month.</p>
                                </section>
                            </div>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <i class="icon icon-plus"></i>
                            <div>
                                <a id="SQL_Database_question3">Example of pricing for an elastic database preset with extra storage capacity</a>
                                <section>
                                    <p>Suppose a 125 eDTU advanced pool is preset with 1TB and that the pool has a storage capacity of 250GB, so its extra storage capacity is: 1TB - 250GB = 774GB. During preview, the unit price of extra storage in the advanced pool is about RMB 1.0812/GB/month, so the price of extra storage is: 774 GB * RMB 1.0812/GB/month = RMB 836.85/month. Therefore, the total price of the database equals RMB 8835.00/month (eDTU) + RMB 836.85/month of extra storage = RMB 9671.85/month.</p>
                                </section>

                            </div>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <i class="icon icon-plus"></i>
                            <div>
                                <a id="SQL_Database_question4">What is the difference between advanced RS and the advanced version? </a>
                                <section>
                                     <p>Advanced versions are specially designed for IO intensive generation workloads that require high availability and zero downtime. Such versions have 99.99% availability supported by service level agreements. They also have fault-tolerant capabilities and can automatically process access and write availability.</p>
                                     <p>Advanced RS (preview) is specially designed for IO intensive workloads that can accept limited durability and low-grade service level agreements. Advanced RS is operated through a few redundant copies, which suggests that a data capture delay of as long as 5 minutes may be needed to recover from backups when potential service failures happen.</p>
                                </section>

                            </div>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <i class="icon icon-plus"></i>
                            <div>
                                <a id="SQL_Database_question5">Does advanced RS have service level agreements? </a>
                                <section>
                                   <p>Advanced RS does not provide service level agreements during public preview. When advanced RS is officially published, its service level agreement will be lower than that of the advanced version.</p>
                                </section>

                            </div>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <i class="icon icon-plus"></i>
                            <div>
                                <a id="SQL_Database_question6">Can advanced RS be upgraded to an advanced version?</a>
                                <section>
                                     <p> Yes, it can be upgraded into advanced version at any time.</p>    
                                </section>

                            </div>
                        </li>
